    signsSymptoms: "HbA1c is a laboratory test for diabetes management. Results guide therapy adjustments.",
    assessment: "HPLC: separates HbA1c based on charge difference. Interferences: hemoglobin variants (HbS, HbC, HbE, HbD) may cause spurious results depending on method. HbF >10%: falsely decreases HbA1c on some methods (HbF is not glycated at the beta-chain N-terminus). Boronate affinity: not affected by hemoglobin variants (measures ALL glycated hemoglobin regardless of variant). Conditions affecting RBC lifespan: shortened lifespan (hemolytic anemia, blood loss) = falsely LOW HbA1c. Prolonged lifespan (iron deficiency, splenectomy) = falsely HIGH HbA1c.",
