    complications: "Hemoglobin variants: method-dependent interference. Labs must know which variants their method can and cannot accurately measure. Conditions altering RBC turnover give misleading results. Fructosamine (glycated albumin): alternative measure reflecting 2-3 weeks of glycemia (useful when HbA1c is unreliable).",
    clinicalPearls: ["HbA1c reflects average glucose over 2-3 MONTHS (RBC lifespan = 120 days)", "Shortened RBC lifespan (hemolytic anemia) = falsely LOW HbA1c; prolonged lifespan (iron deficiency) = falsely HIGH", "Boronate affinity method is NOT affected by hemoglobin variants—use when variants cause interference with HPLC/immunoassay"],
    examPitfalls: ["HbA1c ≥6.5% is a diagnostic criterion for diabetes—must use NGSP-certified method", "HbS and HbC cause method-dependent interference—know YOUR laboratory's method limitations", "Fructosamine measures glycated ALBUMIN (2-3 weeks)—alternative when HbA1c is unreliable (hemolytic anemia, hemoglobinopathies)"],
